    • Method Detail

      • getElementsByIdentifier

        public static java.lang.Iterable<JvmElement> getElementsByIdentifier(PsiElement identifierElement)
        Example 1 
         public class JavaClass {
     public static void <caret>main(String[] args) {}
 }
        In this case there will be a single result: JvmMethod instance corresponding to the main method. Example 2 
         class GroovyClass {
     static void <caret>main(String[] args, whatever = 2) {}
 }
        In this case the result will consist of two JvmMethods corresponding to respective method overload (because in class file there will be two methods).

      • getImmediatelyContainingElements

        public static java.lang.Iterable<JvmElement> getImmediatelyContainingElements(PsiElement place)
        Example 
         class GroovyClass {
     static void main(String[] args, whatever = 2) {<caret>} // note caret is within method body
 }
        In this case the result will consist of two JvmMethods corresponding to respective method overload (because in class file there will be two methods).
